;PROTEIN WAS CRYSTALLISED USING THE VAPOR DIFFUSION METHOD (SITTING DROP). THE WELLS CONTAINED 500 MICROLITERS OF PRECIPITANT SOLUTION AND THE DROPS WERE COMPOSED OF 1.5 MICROLITERS OF PROTEIN SOLUTION (15 MG/ML) AND 1.5 MICROLITERS OF RESERVOIR SOLUTION. THE BEST CRYSTALS WERE OBTAINED FROM A SOLUTION CONTAINING 1.6 M SODIUM MALONATE PH 6 AT 293 K.
;
